the wagtail. Hence the proverb. tumcha inasoan, sai don ja dalli, mameroos jà badda,
masumak ja baas, the northern monsoon approaches; the swallow returns to her house;
the bachelors wish to marry; it is now the time for pairing.

in, somewhere, there: de don, in the house: de Tackais, near Tackais: but the de is commonly
joined to two other words, as lellum, and pana, of which the first means in, and the second there; 
thus instead of the above, they say, de lellum don, pana de Tackais: de is not seldom found 
after innai, and thus serves to point out a place; as innai de errenerren, from Favorlang;
de means also near, paga barron de tabaipaû ja don. Nataroa, mini, de lellum, inni, is of the
same meaning: sometimes i is used, as kakoren i barrien, for lellum.

zinummaat, tadûmmaat, g: daatta, to approach, to draw near. Passi. daatten, dsinaat, inodaatten,
that which is approached. Padaat, to draw near; dûmmadaat, intend. taddaat, a drawing near;
dûmmaat o assaban o sabba, dûmmaat ta deon.

kinûmmiagh, kakūmmiagh, g; kiagcha, I: kiagchen, kiniagch, ino
kiagchen, to stretch out. Kûmmiagh, o asjiel, to stretch out the legs: written gûmmiach; 
magiach, stretched out.

kinûmmomogh, kakûmmomogh, g: kûmmogcha, I: kûmmogchen, 
kinummogh, inokūmmogchen;
this word is only aded to ranied, rima, and riba, signifying to shut up.

mi, ma, racha, rachen, inorachen, to take, to fetch, to receive.
Parach, trans. nom. a reception; 
ma-arrachen, ceiver; mararach, intend.

mi, ma, aripocha, aripochen, inaripoch, inoaripochen, disturbed, fretted;
maripoch, jain_sies, my mind is uneasy.
Paripoch, a disturber.

poor, necessitons; masabba o machan. destitute of food; manabba o arribil, without furniture;
mi, ma, asabba. Sabba,nom. poverty, necessity. Pasabba, imp. asabba. asabban, &c.
pas. ipasabba, &c. to make poor.

minasinasien, mamasinûsien, asinasina, asinasinan; 
inasinan,inoasinasinan, to produce an echo in a church, or a closed chamber.
Pasinasien, trans. Sinasien, an echo.

mi, ma, atabtabba, neutr.
 Highland, as motarror.
 Patabtab, to heighten; act. et trans. imp. atabtabba, atabben;
 inatabtab,inotabtabnen, ipatabtabba, pass. Ipatabtab,&c.
 tabtab, height of land. Neutr. Atabtaban elevating; 
ma-atabtab, one who elevates.

minatea, mayea; 
atea, as machote, and malleak, to undergo punishment,
whereby a person is taught to be more careful in future. Punished.

pinissássen, papissássen, issassena, issassenan, inisassenan, to rest. Paissassen, pi, pa,
ipaissassena, ipaissassen, &c. to cause to rest. Aissassen, rest: aissassenan, time of rest;
aissassenaihan, place of rest.

pinorried, paporried, borrida, borriden, binorried, inoborriden, to turn anything around from the one side 
to another. Borridea ma dich aichoar. zjabaan auniga, put the sick man on the left side; 
jo pizio porried naûpoot a oaloachoa mabachas, you must turn the sheet that it may dry. Paborried, pinaborried, inipaborried, to cause to be turned.
